            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I'm pretty sure this is (partially) a problem on the neovim side. Neovim shouldn't identify `lpeg.so` as the correct library as `.so` files on mac are apparently just `.bundle` files, which can't be linked.\n\nI'm not familiar with mac so I'll need to investigate on best way to solve this. If mac also uses the `lib` prefix for their dynamic libraries it might be worth skipping all shared libraries that don't have a `lib` prefix. Otherwise I can probably solve this by explicitly searching for `.dylib` extension or something.",
